Unable to match Atiku's $20,000 dollars to each delegate at the convention and other big Dollar spenders in the PDP primaries; the same Atiku that he was Vice presidential candidate to, in the 2019 General Elections, Peter Obi chose to cross carpet to the Labour Party (LP). With little or no competition, he was able to fulfill all of the under the table demands of the labour bureaucrats to become the presidential flag bearer of the LP.